headline.main: EUROPEAN NEWS.; THE JASON AT ST. JOHNS. FURTHER BY THE PERSIA. THE GREAT EASTERN. Safety and Success of our Minister in China.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Jason, from Galway on the evening of the 17th October, arrived at St. Johns, N. B., at 12 o'clock on Monday night, and sailed at 11 o'clock next morning, for New-York. The royal mail steamship America, from Boston via Halifax, arrived at Liverpool on the 15th.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Jason, from Galway on the atternoon of Oct. 17, arrived at St. Johns on Monday evening. She brings the gratifying intelligence that the American Minister, Mr. WARD, has been courteously received and entertained at Peking, and that he had strong hopes of sending home the ratified treaty by the next steamer.

headline.main: NEWS BY TELEGRAPH.; The Brownsville Melee-Negotiations with the Liberal Government of Mexico--Financial Statements. TOPICS AT WASHINGTON.

docs.lead_paragraph: Secretary CASS is in the receipt of a letter from tile Mexican Consul at Brownsville, Texas, stating that the insurgents at that place were all American citizens, though Mexicans by birth. They reside in Texas, and only four of them passed over into Mexico. The Consul visited their chief in person, and induced them to disperse.
